indication: Cromoglicic acid is a medication used to treat asthma, allergic reactions of the eyes and nose, as well as other mast cell reactions.

name: Ganciclovir
indication: Ganciclovir is a DNA polymerase inhibitor used to treat cytomegalovirus and herpetic keratitis of the eye.

name: Hydroxyurea
indication: Hydroxyurea is an antimetabolite used to treat sickle cell anemia crisis.

name: Letrozole
indication: Letrozole is an aromatase inhibitor used to treat breast cancer in postmenopausal women.

name: Tioconazole
indication: Tioconazole is an imidazole antifungal used to treat vulvovaginal candidiasis.

name: Busulfan
indication: Busulfan is an alkylating agent used to treat chronic myelogenous leukemia.

name: Ketoprofen
indication: Ketoprofen is an NSAID used to treat rheumatoid arthritis, osteoarthritis, ankylosing spondylitis, dysmenorrhea, mild to moderate muscle pain, postoperative pain, and postpartum pain.

name: Edrophonium
indication: Edrophonium is a cholinesterase inhibitor used to diagnose and evaluate myasthenia gravis.

name: Metyrapone
indication: Metyrapone is a steroid 11-beta-monooxygenase inhibitor used to test hypothalamic-pituitary ACTH function.

name: Cinacalcet
indication: Cinacalcet is a calcium sensing receptor agonist used to treat secondary hyperparathyroidism in chronic kidney disease and hypercalcemia in parathyroid carcinoma.

name: Clobetasol propionate
indication: Clobetasol propionate is a corticosteroid used to treat corticosteroid-responsive dermatoses and plaque psoriasis.

name: Balsalazide
indication: Balsalazide is an aminosalicylate used to treat ulcerative colitis.

name: Sulfamethoxazole
indication: Sulfamethoxazole is an oral sulfonamide antibiotic, given in combination with trimethoprim, used to treat a variety of infections of the urinary tract, respiratory system, and gastrointestinal tract.

name: Glyburide
indication: Glyburide is a sulfonylurea used in the treatment of non insulin dependent diabetes mellitus.

name: Minocycline
indication: Minocycline is a tetracycline analog used to treat a wide variety of infections in the body.

name: Guanfacine
indication: Guanfacine is an alpha-2A adrenergic receptor agonist used to treat ADHD.

name: Bethanechol
indication: Bethanechol is a muscarinic agonist used to treat postoperative and postpartum nonobstructive functional urinary retention and neurogenic atony of the bladder with retention.

name: Isosorbide mononitrate
indication: Isosorbide mononitrate is a nitrate used to prevent and treat angina and to treat angina caused by coronary artery disease.

name: Trichlormethiazide
indication: Used in the treatment of oedema (including that associated with heart failure) and hypertension

name: Phylloquinone
indication: Vitamin K1 is a fat soluble vitamin used to treat hemorrhagic conditions in infants and coumarin overdoses.

name: Felodipine
indication: Felodipine is a calcium channel blocker used to treat hypertension.

name: Mycophenolic acid
indication: Mycophenolic acid is an immunosuppressant used to prevent organ transplant rejections.

name: Amlexanox
indication: Used as a paste in the mouth to treat aphthous ulcers (canker sores)

name: Ketoconazole
indication: Ketoconazole is a broad spectrum antifungal used to treat seborrheic dermatitis and fungal skin infections.

name: Methoxyflurane
indication: For use in the induction and maintenance of general anesthesia

name: Irbesartan
indication: Irbesartan is an angiotensin receptor blocker used to treat hypertension, delay progression of diabetic nephropathy, and treat congestive heart failure.

name: Topotecan
indication: Topotecan is an antineoplastic agent used to treat ovarian cancer, small cell lung cancer, or cervical cancer.

name: Ethinamate
indication: Used for the short-term treatment of insomnia, however, it generally has been replaced by other sedative-hypnotic agents

name: Probenecid
indication: Probenecid is a medication used to treat gouty arthritis, tophaceous gout, and hyperuricemia.

name: Mercaptopurine
indication: Mercaptopurine is an antineoplastic agent used to treat acute lymphocytic leukemia.

name: Procainamide
indication: Procainamide is a medication used to treat life threatening ventricular arrhythmias.

name: Tolterodine
indication: Tolterodine is a muscarinic receptor antagonist used to treat overactive bladder with urinary incontinence, urgency, and frequency.

name: Selegiline
indication: Selegiline is a monoamine oxidase inhibitor used to treat major depressive disorder and Parkinson's.

name: Fenofibrate
indication: Fenofibrate is a peroxisome proliferator receptor alpha activator used to lower LDL-C, total-C, triglycerides, and Apo B, while increasing HDL-C in hypercholesterolemia, dyslipidemia, and hypertriglyceridemia.

name: Thalidomide
indication: Thalidomide is a medication used to treat cancers, particularly newly diagnosed multiple myeloma, and erythema nodosum leprosum.

name: Melphalan
indication: Melphalan is an alkylating antineoplastic agent used for high-dose conditioning prior to hematopoietic stem cell transplant in patients with multiple myeloma.

name: Memantine
indication: Memantine is an NMDA receptor antagonist used to treat moderate to severe dementia in Alzheimer's.

name: Gatifloxacin
indication: Gatifloxacin is a fourth generation fluoroquinolone used to treat a wide variety of infections in the body.

name: Rifampicin
indication: Rifampicin is an antibiotic used to treat several types of mycobacterial infections including Mycobacterium avium complex, leprosy, and in combination with other antibacterials to treat latent or active tuberculosis.

name: Lubiprostone
indication: Lubiprostone is a prostaglandin derivative used to treat constipation caused by irritable bowel syndrome and opioid-use.

name: Fluocinonide
indication: Fluocinonide is a high potency corticosteroid commonly used topically for a number of inflammatory skin conditions.

name: Abacavir
indication: Abacavir is an antiviral nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor used in combination with other antiretrovirals for the treatment of HIV.

name: Ibuprofen
indication: Ibuprofen is an NSAID and non-selective COX inhibitor used to treat mild-moderate pain, fever, and inflammation.

name: Novobiocin
indication: For the treatment of infections due to staphylococci and other susceptible organisms

name: Benzylpenicillin
indication: Benzylpenicillin is a penicillin used for the treatment of infections caused by gram-positive cocci, in particular streptococcal infections. This form of penicillin is typically used in intravenous or long-acting injectable formulations due to poor oral absorption.

name: Nitrendipine
indication: Nitrendipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker indicated in the treatment of arterial hypertension.

name: Tocainide
indication: Tocainide is an orally active class 1b antiarrhythmic agent that interferes with cardiac sodium channels and typically used to treat ventricular arrhythmias.

name: Echothiophate
indication: Echothiophate is an acetylcholinesterase inhibitor used in ophthalmic preparations to increase the drainage of intraocular fluid; most commonly used for the treatment of glaucoma.

name: Praziquantel
indication: Praziquantel is an anthelmintic medication used to treat a number of parasitic worm infections such as schistosomiasis.

name: Norfloxacin
indication: Norfloxacin is a broad-spectrum fluoroquinolone antibiotic with variable activity against gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria. Typically reserved for the treatment of UTIs due to accumulation in the urine.

name: Amoxicillin
indication: Amoxicillin is a penicillin derivative used for the treatment of infections caused by gram-positive bacteria, in particular streptococcal bacteria causing upper respiratory tract infections.

name: Azlocillin
indication: For the treatment of infections caused by Pseudomonas aeruginosa, Escherichia coli, and Haemophilus influenzae

name: Oxybutynin
indication: Oxybutynin is an antimuscarinic agent that reduces detrusor muscle activity, relaxing the bladder and preventing the urge to void.

name: Acetophenazine
indication: For the treatment of disorganized and psychotic thinking

name: Isoprenaline
indication: Isoprenaline is a catecholamine non-selective beta-adrenergic agonist typically used to treat bradycardia and heart block.

name: Melatonin
indication: Melatonin is an endogenous hormone produced by the pineal gland that regulates sleep-wake cycles and when provided exogenously has beneficial effects on sleep-onset latency; available as an over-the-counter supplement.

name: Cefditoren
indication: Cefditoren is a broad-spectrum third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic typically used to treat bacterial infections of the skin and respiratory tract.

name: Glipizide
indication: Glipizide is a sulfonylurea medication used in Type 2 Diabetes to sensitize pancreatic beta cells and stimulate insulin release.

name: Clonazepam
indication: Clonazepam is a long-acting benzodiazepine with intermediate onset commonly used to treat panic disorders, severe anxiety, and seizures.

name: Promethazine
indication: Promethazine is a first-generation antihistamine used for the treatment of allergic conditions, nausea and vomiting, and motion sickness.

name: Dihydrotachysterol
indication: Dihydrotachysterol is a synthetic analog of vitamin D that does not require renal activation like vitamin D2 or Vitamin D3.

name: Atazanavir
indication: Atazanavir is an antiviral protease inhibitor used in combination with other antiretrovirals for the treatment of HIV.

name: Fludarabine
indication: Fludarabine is a purine analog antimetabolite that inhibits DNA synthesis.

name: Perhexiline
indication: For the management of severe angina pectoris

name: Diphenhydramine
indication: Diphenhydramine is a H1 receptor antihistamine used in the treatment of seasonal allergies, and various allergic reactions including sneezing, runny nose, itchy/watery eyes, itching of nose or throat, pruritus, urticaria, insect bites/stings, and allergic rashes.

name: Atorvastatin
indication: Atorvastatin is an HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor used to lower lipid levels and reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease including myocardial infarction and stroke.

name: Etidronic acid
indication: Etidronic acid is a bisphosphonate drug that prevents osteoclastic bone resorption; used for the prevention and treatment of osteoporosis.

name: Deslanoside
indication: For the treatment and management of Congestive cardiac insufficiency, arrhythmias and heart failure

name: Tegaserod
indication: Tegaserod is a serotonin-4 (5-HT4) receptor agonist indicated for the treatment of constipation predominant irritable bowel syndrome (IBS-C) specifically in women under the age of 65. There is currently no safety or efficacy data for use of tegaserol in men.

name: Vigabatrin
indication: Vigabatrin is an irreversible GABA transaminase inhibitor used as an adjunct therapy to treat refractory complex partial seizures in patients ≥2 years unresponsive to alternatives. May also be used as monotherapy to treat infantile spasms in infants 1 month to 2 years.

name: Diphenoxylate
indication: Diphenoxylate is an antidiarrheal medication used with atropine to manage diarrhea.

name: Streptomycin
indication: Streptomycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic indicated to treat multi-drug resistant mycobacterium tuberculosis and various non-tuberculosis infections.

name: Orlistat
indication: Orlistat is a reversible inhibitor of gastrointestinal lipases indicated for weight loss and weight maintenance.

name: Emedastine
indication: Emedastine is a selective H1-receptor antagonist used topically to manage symptoms of allergic conjunctivitis.

name: Pilocarpine
indication: Pilocarpine is a muscarinic cholinergic agonist used on the eye to treat elevated intraocular pressure, various types of glaucoma, and to induce miosis. Also available orally to treat symptoms of dry mouth associated with Sjogren's syndrome and radiotherapy.

name: Benzocaine
indication: Benzocaine is a topical local anesthetic used for the temporary relief of pain and itching associated with minor burns, sunburn, scrapes and insect bites or minor skin irritations.

name: Primaquine
indication: Primaquine is an antimalarial indicated to prevent relapse of vivax malaria.

name: Iloprost
indication: Iloprost is a synthetic prostacyclin analog indicated to treat pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH).

name: Deserpidine
indication: Deserpidine is an alkaloid that has been used to manage hypertension.

name: Pentolinium
indication: Used to produce controlled hypotension during surgical procedures and in hypertensive crises

name: Butenafine
indication: Butenafine is a topical antifungal used to treat tinea versicolor, tinea pedis, tinea cruris, and tinea corporis.

name: Ouabain
indication: For the treatment of atrial fibrillation and flutter and heart failure

name: Dimethyl sulfoxide
indication: Dimethyl sulfoxide is a reversible mitogen-activated extracellular signal-regulated kinase-1 (MEK1) and MEK2 inhibitor used to treat certain types of melanoma, metastatic non-small cell lung cancer, and locally advanced or metastatic anaplastic thyroid cancer.

name: Fluvastatin
indication: Fluvastatin is an HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor used to lower lipid levels and reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease including myocardial infarction and stroke.

name: Oxamniquine
indication: For treatment of Schistosomiasis caused by Schistosoma mansoni

name: Leflunomide
indication: Leflunomide is a pyrimidine synthesis inhibitor indicated to treat rheumatoid arthritis.

name: Rosuvastatin
indication: Rosuvastatin is an HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor used to lower lipid levels and reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease including myocardial infarction and stroke.

name: Flucytosine
indication: Flucytosine is an antifungal indicated only to treat severe infections throughout the body caused by susceptible strains of Candida or Cryptococcus.

name: Pimozide
indication: Pimozide is an antipsychotic used to manage debilitating motor and phonic tics in patients with Tourette's Disorder.

name: Capecitabine
indication: Capecitabine is a nucleoside metabolic inhibitor indicated to treat different gastrointestinal, including pancreatic cancer, and breast cancer.

name: Arbutamine
indication: Used to elicit acute cardiovascular responses (cardiac stumulant), similar to those produced by exercise, in order to aid in diagnosing the presence or absence of coronary artery disease (CAD) in patients who cannot exercise adequately

name: Sertraline
indication: Sertraline is a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) indicated to treat major depressive disorder, social anxiety disorder and many other psychiatric conditions.

name: Sibutramine
indication: Sibutramine is a norepinephrine, serotonin and dopamine reuptake inhibitor indicated to assist with weight loss in obesity.

name: Levocabastine
indication: Levocabastine is a selective histamine H1 receptor antagonist indicated for the management of seasonal allergic conjunctivitis symptoms.

name: Methyprylon
indication: For the treatment of insomnia

name: Trilostane
indication: Used in the treatment of Cushing's syndrome

name: Miconazole
indication: Miconazole is an azole antifungal with broad-spectrum activity used to treat fungal infections affecting the vagina, mouth and skin, including candidiasis.

name: Colistimethate
indication: Colistimethate is an antibiotic indicated for treatment of infections caused by susceptible strains of certain gram-negative bacilli. It is particularly useful for targeting sensitive strains of Pseudomonas aeruginosa.

name: Cefuroxime
indication: Cefuroxime is a cephalosporin indicated for the treatment of a variety of infections including acute bacterial otitis media, several upper respiratory tract infections, skin infections, urinary tract infections, gonorrhea, early Lyme disease, and impetigo.

name: Papaverine
indication: Papaverine is an alkaloid used to treat many types of smooth muscle spasms such as "vascular spasms" associated with acute myocardial infarction and angina pectoris, as well as "visceral spasms".

name: Chlorpheniramine
indication: Chlorpheniramine is a histamine-H1 receptor antagonist indicated for the management of symptoms associated with upper respiratory allergies.

name: Nifedipine
indication: Nifedipine is a dihydropyridine calcium channel blocker indicated for the management of several subtypes of angina pectoris, and hypertension.

name: Trimethaphan
indication: For the controlled reduction of blood pressure during surgery and in the treatment of hypertensive emergencies

name: Atovaquone
indication: Atovaquone is an antimicrobial indicated for the prevention and treatment of Pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia (PCP) and for the prevention and treatment of Plasmodium falciparum malaria.

name: Amiodarone
indication: Amiodarone is a class III antiarrhythmic indicated for the treatment of recurrent hemodynamically unstable ventricular tachycardia and recurrent ventricular fibrillation.

name: Diazoxide
indication: Diazoxide is a non diuretic benzothiadiazine indicated for the management of hypoglycemia in patients who produce an excess of insulin caused by a variety of conditions.

name: Gliclazide
indication: Gliclazide is a sulfonylurea used to treat hyperglycemia in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Phenacemide
indication: Used to control certain seizures in the treatment of epilepsy

name: Ambenonium
indication: Ambenonium is a cholinesterase inhibitor that targets both muscarinic and nicotinic receptors indicated for the treatment of myasthenia gravis.

name: Proflavine
indication: Proflavine is a topical antiseptic agent used in wound dressings to prevent infections.

name: Tolbutamide
indication: Tolbutamide is a sulfonylurea used to treat hyperglycemia in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Anisindione
indication: For the prophylaxis and treatment of venous thrombosis and its extension, the treatment of atrial fibrillation with embolization, the prophylaxis and treatment of pulmonary embolism, and as an adjunct in the treatment of coronary occlusion

name: Dutasteride
indication: Dutasteride is an antiandrogenic compound that is used for the treatment of symptomatic benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) in adult males by inhibiting 5-alpha reductase.

name: Econazole
indication: Econazole is a topical antifungal used to treat tinea pedis, tinea cruris, tinea corporis, cutaneous candidiasis and tinea versicolor.

name: Bicalutamide
indication: Bicalutamide is an androgen receptor inhibitor used to treat Stage D2 metastatic carcinoma of the prostate.

name: Rabeprazole
indication: Rabeprazole is a proton pump inhibitor used to help gastrointestinal ulcers heal, to treat symptoms of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), to eradicate Helicobacter pylori, and to treat hypersecretory conditions such as Zollinger-Ellison Syndrome.

name: Prednicarbate
indication: Prednicarbate is a medium potency topical corticosteroid used to manage pruritus and inflammation associated with responsive skin conditions.

name: Proguanil
indication: Proguanil is a medication indicated for prophylaxis and treatment of Plasmodium falciparum malaria.

name: Pioglitazone
indication: Pioglitazone is a thiazolidinedione used adjunctively with diet and exercise to normalize glycemic levels in adults with type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Tiludronic acid
indication: Tiludronic acid is a bisphosphonate used for the treatment of Paget's disease of bone.

name: Desoxycorticosterone pivalate
indication: Examined for treatment of adrenocortical insufficiency especially in multiple sclerosis, congenital cerebral palsy, polyarteritis nodosa, and rheumatoid arthritis

name: Doxacurium
indication: Doxacurium chloride is a nondepolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent used as an adjunct to general anesthesia to facilitate tracheal intubation, and to provide skeletal muscle relaxation during surgical procedures.

name: Carvedilol
indication: Carvedilol is a non selective beta-adrenergic antagonist used to treat mild to severe chronic heart failure, hypertension, and left ventricular dysfunction following myocardial infarction in clinically stable patients.

name: Levofloxacin
indication: Levofloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic used to treat infections caused by susceptible bacteria of the upper respiratory tract, skin and skin structures, urinary tract, and prostate, as well as for post-exposure treatment of inhaled anthrax and the plague.

name: Sulfinpyrazone
indication: Sulfinpyrazone is a platelet inhibitory and uricosuric agent used to inhibit thrombotic and embolic processes and to manage the chronic phases of gout .

name: Cefapirin
indication: Cefapirin is a first generation cephalosporin indicated in the treatment of susceptible bacterial infections.

name: Cefadroxil
indication: Cefadroxil is a cephalosporin antibiotic used in the treatment of various bacterial infections, such as urinary tract infections, skin and skin structure infections, and tonsillitis.

name: Micafungin
indication: Micafungin is an antifungal agent used for the treatment of candidemia, acute disseminated candidiasis, and certain other invasive Candida infections, and for the prophylaxis of Candida infections during stem cell transplantation.

name: Doxepin
indication: Doxepin is a psychotropic agent used for the treatment of depression, anxiety, manic-depressive disorder, and insomnia.

name: Amifostine
indication: Amifostine is a cytoprotective adjuvant used for reduction in the cumulative renal toxicity in patients with ovarian cancer and moderate to severe xerostomia in patients undergoing post-operative radiation treatment for head and neck cancer.

name: Diclofenamide
indication: Diclofenamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor used for the management of open-angle and secondary glaucoma, as well as acute angle-closure glaucoma in delayed pre-operative setting requiring a reduction in intraocular pressure.

name: Sulfoxone
indication: For the treatment of leprosy and dermatitis herpetiformis

name: Diphenylpyraline
indication: Diphenylpyraline is an antihistamine used for the treatment of allergic rhinitis, hay fever, and allergic skin disorders.

name: Cloxacillin
indication: Cloxacillin is an antibiotic agent used for the treatment of beta-hemolytic streptococcal and pneumococcal infections as well as staphylococcal infections.

name: Flavoxate
indication: Flavoxate is a muscarinic antagonist and spasmolytic used for the symptomatic relief of conditions associated with lack of muscle control in the bladder, such as dysuria, urgency, and nocturia.

name: Nefazodone
indication: Nefazodone is an antidepressant used in the treatment of depression.

name: Cefprozil
indication: Cefprozil is a cephalosporin antibiotic used in the treatment of various bacterial infections, such as pharyngitis, tonsillitis, otitis media, and uncomplicated skin infections.

name: Desipramine
indication: Desipramine is a tricyclic antidepressant used in the treatment of depression.

name: Candicidin
indication: Used in the topical treatment of vulvovaginal candidiasis

name: Sertaconazole
indication: Sertaconazole is a topical antifungal agent used in the treatment of interdigital tinea pedis in immunocompetent patients.

name: Thiamylal
indication: Used for the production of complete anaesthesia of short duration, for the induction of general anaesthesia, and for inducing a hypnotic state

name: Gemifloxacin
indication: Gemifloxacin is a quinolone antibacterial agent used for the treatment of acute bacterial exacerbation of chronic bronchitis and mild to moderate community-acquired pneumonia caused by susceptible bacteria.

name: Bupropion
indication: Bupropion is a norepinephrine and dopamine reuptake inhibitor used in the treatment of major depressive disorder (MDD), seasonal affective disorder (SAD), and as an aid to smoking cessation.

name: Trimetrexate
indication: Trimetrexate is a folate antagonist used for the treatment of moderate-to-severe Pneumocystis carinii pneumonia (PCP) in immunocompromised patients as an alternative therapy in combination with leucovorin.

name: Bretylium
indication: Bretylium is a norepinephrine release inhibitor used for the prophylaxis and therapy of ventricular fibrillation, as well as the treatment of life-threatening ventricular arrhythmias.

name: Halothane
indication: Halothane is a general inhalation anesthetic used for the induction and maintenance of general anesthesia.

name: Dinoprost tromethamine
indication: Used for aborting second-trimester pregnancy (between the twelfth to eighteenth week of gestation) and in incomplete abortion or for therapeutic abortion in cases of intrauterine fetal death and congenital abnormalities incompatible with life

name: Chloroprocaine
indication: Chloroprocaine is a local anesthetic agent indicated for intrathecal injection in adults for the production of subarachnoid block, spinal anesthesia, or ocular surface anesthesia.

name: Terazosin
indication: Terazosin is an alpha-1 adrenergic antagonist used in the treatment of symptomatic benign prostatic hyperplasia and management of hypertension.

name: Calcium chloride
indication: Calcium chloride is an ionic compound used for the treatment of hypocalcemia and hyperkalemia, and as an antidote to magnesium intoxication due to overdosage of magnesium sulfate.

name: Ofloxacin
indication: Ofloxacin is an antibacterial agent used for the treatment of bacterial infections in many parts of the body, including the respiratory tract, kidney, skin, soft tissue, and urinary tract.

name: Cilostazol
indication: Cilostazol is an antiplatelet agent and vasodilator used for the symptomatic relief of intermittent claudication.

name: Itraconazole
indication: Itraconazole is an antifungal agent used for the treatment of various fungal infections in immunocompromised and non-immunocompromised patients, such as pulmonary and extrapulmonary blastomycosis, histoplasmosis, and onychomycosis.

name: Procarbazine
indication: Procarbazine is an antineoplastic agent indicated for the treatment of stage III and stage IV Hodgkin's disease in combination with other chemotherapeutic agents.

name: Arsenic trioxide
indication: Arsenic trioxide is a chemotherapeutic agent used in the treatment of refractory or relapsed acute promyelocytic leukemia in patients with prior retinoid and anthracycline chemotherapy.

name: Guanethidine
indication: Guanethidine is an antihypertensive agent used in the management of moderate and severe hypertension, either alone or as an adjunct, and for the management of renal hypertension.

name: Moclobemide
indication: Moclobemide is a monoamine oxidase inhibitor used in the treatment of major depressive disorder and bipolar disorder.

name: Kanamycin
indication: Kanamycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic agent used in the treatment of various infections caused by susceptible bacteria.

name: Orphenadrine
indication: Orphenadrine is a muscarinic antagonist used as an adjunct for the symptomatic relief of musculoskeletal pain and discomfort.

name: Phenobarbital
indication: Phenobarbital is a long-lasting barbiturate and anticonvulsant used in the treatment of all types of seizures, except for absent seizures.

name: Escitalopram
indication: Escitalopram is a selective serotonin re-uptake inhibitor used in the treatment of major depressive disorder (MDD), generalized anxiety disorder (GAD), and other select psychiatric disorders such as obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD).

name: Cyclizine
indication: Cyclizine is an antihistamine and antiemetic drug used for the prevention and treatment of nausea, vomiting, and dizziness associated with motion sickness, and vertigo.

name: Idarubicin
indication: Idarubicin is an anthracycline antineoplastic agent used to treat acute myeloid leukemia (AML) in adults.

name: Chlormezanone
indication: Used in the management of anxiety and in the treatment of muscle spasm

name: Podofilox
indication: Podofilox is a topical agent used for the treatment of external genital warts and perianal warts.

name: Rescinnamine
indication: For the treatment of hypertension

name: Ifosfamide
indication: Ifosfamide is an alkylating and immunosuppressive agent used in chemotherapy for the treatment of cancers, including testicular cancer, ovarian cancer, cervical cancer, osteocarcinoma, bladder cancer, small cell lung cancer, and non-Hodgkin's lymphoma.

name: Propafenone
indication: Propafenone is a Class 1C antiarrhythmic agent used in the management of paroxysmal atrial fibrillation/flutter and ventricular arrhythmias.

name: Naloxone
indication: Naloxone is an opioid receptor antagonist used to rapidly reverse an opioid overdose. Also included in some drug formulations as an abuse deterrent to prevent injection.

name: Domperidone
indication: Domperidone is a dopamine receptor antagonist used as a peristaltic stimulant and anti-emetic agent for dyspepsia, indigestion, epigastric pain, nausea, and vomiting.

name: Fluoxymesterone
indication: Fluoxymesterone is a synthetic androgenic anabolic steroid that used in the treatment of hypogonadism and delayed puberty in males, as well as breast neoplasms in women.

name: Pergolide
indication: Pergolide is a long-acting dopamine agonist that is uncommonly used for the management of Parkinson's disease, due to the risk for cardiac valvulopathy.

name: Iophendylate
indication: Iophendylate is used as a contrast agent to locate spinal tumors

name: Ciclopirox
indication: Ciclopirox is a broad-spectrum topical antifungal agent used to treat mild to moderate onychomycosis of fingernails and toenails in immunocompetent patients.

name: Desflurane
indication: Desflurane is a general inhalation anesthetic for inpatient and outpatient surgery in adults.

name: Clindamycin
indication: Clindamycin is a lincosamide antibiotic used to treat serious infections caused by susceptible anaerobic, streptococcal, staphylococcal, and pneumococcal bacteria.

name: Dexfenfluramine
indication: For the management of obesity including weight loss and maintenance of weight loss in patients on a reduced calorie diet

name: Oxymorphone
indication: Oxymorphone is an opioid analgesic used in the management of moderate-to-severe pain and for analgesic therapies.

name: Acebutolol
indication: Acebutolol is a selective β1-receptor antagonist used for the management of hypertension and ventricular premature beats in adults.

name: Brinzolamide
indication: Brinzolamide is a carbonic anhydrase inhibitor used for the reduction of elevated intraocular pressure in patients with ocular hypertension or open-angle glaucoma.

name: Flecainide
indication: Flecainide is a class Ic antiarrhythmic agent used to manage atrial fibrillation and paroxysmal supraventricular tachycardias (PSVT).

name: Estramustine
indication: Estramustine is an antineoplastic agent used for the management of metastatic and/or progressive prostate cancer in palliative setting.

name: Captopril
indication: Captopril is an ACE inhibitor used for the management of essential or renovascular hypertension, congestive heart failure, left ventricular dysfunction following myocardial infarction, and nephropathy.

name: Zopiclone
indication: Zopiclone is a nonbenzodiazepine hypnotic used for the short-term management of insomnia.

name: Bromocriptine
indication: Bromocriptine is a dopamine D2 receptor agonist used for the treatment of galactorrhea due to hyperprolactinemia and other prolactin-related conditions, as well as in early Parkinsonian Syndrome.

name: Rifapentine
indication: Rifapentine is an antibiotic agent used in the treatment of pulmonary tuberculosis.

name: Levetiracetam
indication: Levetiracetam is a novel anticonvulsant agent used as an adjunct medication to manage partial onset, myoclonic, and generalized tonic-clonic seizures in patients with epilepsy.

name: Nadolol
indication: Nadolol is a non-selective beta-adrenergic antagonist used for the management of arrhythmias, angina pectoris, and hypertension.

name: Mitoxantrone
indication: Mitoxantrone is a chemotherapeutic agent used for the treatment of secondary progressive, progressive relapsing, or worsening relapsing-remitting multiple sclerosis.

name: Flumazenil
indication: Flumazenil is a benzodiazepine antagonist that is used for the complete or partial reversal of the sedative effects caused by benzodiazepines in various clinical settings, such as induced general anesthesia for diagnostic and therapeutic procedures.

name: Lomustine
indication: Lomustine is an alkylating agent used as a part of chemotherapeutic regimens for the treatment of primary and metastatic brain tumors as well as refractory or relapsed Hodgkin's disease in addition to surgical and/or radiotherapeutic treatments.

name: Sparfloxacin
indication: Sparfloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic used to treat bacterial respiratory infections and sinusitis.

name: Dezocine
indication: Indicated in the treatment of moderate to severe pain
