name: Dalfopristin
indication: Dalfopristin is an antibiotic used with quinupristin to treat severe or life-threatening infections of vancomycin-resistant Enterococcus faecium (VREF), and skin infections caused by methicillin susceptible staphylococcus aureus or streptococcus pyogenes.

name: Pantothenic acid
indication: Pantothenic acid is a vitamin B5 found in various nutritional supplements.

name: D-glucose
indication: D-glucose is a most commonly occurring isomer of glucose used as a carbohydrate supplementation in case of nutrient deprivation and metabolic disorders, such as hypoglycemia.

name: Taurine
indication: Taurine is an ingredient found in mixture products indicated for nutritional support.

name: Calcipotriol
indication: Calcipotriol is a topical synthetic vitamin D2 derivative used in the treatment of plaque psoriasis.

name: Vorinostat
indication: Vorinostat is a histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitor used for the treatment of cutaneous manifestations in patients with progressive, persistent, or recurrent cutaneous T- cell lymphoma (CTCL) following prior systemic therapies.

name: Cholic Acid
indication: Cholic Acid is a bile acid used for the treatment of bile acid synthesis disorders due to single enzyme defects and as an adjunctive treatment of peroxisomal disorders with disrupted liver function.

name: Fusidic acid
indication: Fusidic acid is a topical antibacterial agent used to prevent and treat mild to moderate skin infections caused by susceptible bacteria.

name: Oxitriptan
indication: Oxitriptan is a naturally occurring amino acid that is used to manage post-hypoxic myoclonus.

name: Pidolic acid
indication: There is currently no clinically approved and/or marketed medicine that relies upon pidolic acid as an active ingredient for any formal therapeutic indication

name: Acetylcholine
indication: Acetylcholine is a parasympathomimetic neurotransmitter used to induce miosis of the iris in seconds after delivery of the lens in cataract surgery, in penetrating keratoplasty, iridectomy and other anterior segment surgery where rapid miosis may be required.

name: Flavin adenine dinucleotide
indication: Flavin adenine dinucleotide is a coenzyme form of vitamin B2 used in clinical conditions associated with vitamin B2 deficiency.

name: Acetic acid
indication: Acetic acid is an antimicrobial agent used to treat susceptible infections of the external auditory canal.

name: Oteracil
indication: Oteracil is a chemotherapy agent used in combination with tegafur, cisplatin and gimeracil to treat advanced gastric cancer.

name: Phenol
indication: Phenol is an antiseptic and disinfectant used in a variety of settings.

name: Deoxycholic acid
indication: Deoxycholic acid is a cytolytic agent injected subcutaneously to improve the appearance submental fat.

name: Tromethamine
indication: Tromethamine is a proton acceptor used for the prevention and correction of metabolic acidosis associated with various clinical conditions, such as cardiac bypass surgery.

name: Doconexent
indication: Doconexent is an omega 3 fatty acid used in a variety of nutritional supplements to support central nervous system and cardiovascular health.

name: Propanoic acid
indication: Propanoic acid is an antimicrobial food additive.

name: Formaldehyde
indication: Formaldehyde is a naturally occurring hazardous organic compound used as a preservative in animal feed, cosmetic products, laboratory procedures, disinfection, and home building products.

name: Urea
indication: Urea is a keratolytic emollient used to treat hyperkeratotic lesions and moisturize the skin.

name: Dequalinium
indication: Dequalinium is a quaternary ammonium cation antimicrobial agent used to treat common infections of the mouth and throat, as well as vaginal candidiasis.

name: Carbocisteine
indication: Carbocisteine is a expectorant mucolytic used in the relief of respiratory of COPD and other conditions associated with increased mucus viscosity.

name: Lactic acid
indication: Lactic acid is an emollient and keratolytic used agent in various cosmetic products and used as an additive in various pharmaceutical products for its antibacterial properties.

name: Latamoxef
indication: Latamoxef is an oxacephem antibiotic usually grouped with the cephalosporins

name: Trioxsalen
indication: Trioxsalen is a psoralen derivative that has been used in combination with UV light to treat vitiligo, but has been discontinued by its manufacturer.

name: Thiotepa
indication: Thiotepa is an alkylating agent used to prevent graft rejection in stem cell transplantation and to treat a variety of malignancies including certain types of adenocarcinoma and superficial bladder carcinomas.

name: Estriol
indication: Estriol is a weak estrogen used to treat vaginal dryness and estrogen deficiency conditions, such as vaginitis and vulvar itching.

name: Estrone sulfate
indication: Estrone sulfate is an estrogen used as monotherapy or in several combination hormone replacement products for managing menopause symptoms and hormone disorders.

name: Quinestrol
indication: Used in hormone replacement therapy, treating symptoms of menopause such as hot flashes

name: Apramycin
indication: Apramycin is an aminoglycoside antibiotic for veterinary use that is used to treat infections in animals.

name: Iodipamide
indication: Iodipamide is a contrast agent used in cholangiography and cholecystography.

name: Nimesulide
indication: Nimesulide is a cyclooxygenase 2 inhibitor used to treat acute pain and primary dysmenorrhea.

name: Bifonazole
indication: Bifonazole is an azole antifungal drug used to treat fungal skin infections, such as dermatomycosis.

name: Clioquinol
indication: Clioquinol is an antifungal cream used to treat a variety of fungal infections.

name: Metamizole
indication: Metamizole is an antipyretic and analgesic drug used to relieve severe and persistent fever and pain.

name: Phenolphthalein
indication: Phenolphthalein is a drug used for symptomatic relief of constipation and bowel cleansing prior to medical procedures.

name: Zimelidine
indication: For the treatment of depression

name: Rapacuronium
indication: Rapacuronium is a nondepolarizing neuromuscular blocking agent used as an adjunct to general anesthesia to facilitate tracheal intubation, and to provide skeletal muscle relaxation during surgical procedures.

name: Maraviroc
indication: Maraviroc is a CCR5 co-receptor antagonist used with other antiretroviral medications to treat CCR5-tropic HIV-1 infection.

name: Clofedanol
indication: Clofedanol is an antitussive used for the symptomatic relief of acute cough caused by minor throat and bronchial irritation.

name: Cyclandelate
indication: Cyclandelate is a vasodilator used for the treatment of various blood vessel diseases, such as claudication and arteriosclerosis.

name: Cyproterone acetate
indication: Cyproterone acetate is a steroid used in combination with ethinyl estradiol to treat women with severe acne and symptoms of androgenization. Also used alone at much higher doses for palliative treatment of patients with prostate cancer

name: Debrisoquine
indication: For the treatment of moderate and severe hypertension, either alone or as an adjunct, and for the treatment of renal hypertension

name: Flunarizine
indication: Flunarizine is a selective calcium-entry blocker used as migraine prophylaxis in patients with severe and frequent episodes who have not responded adequately to more common treatments.

name: Fluspirilene
indication: Fluspirilene is an antipsychotic agent used in the treatment of schizophrenia.

name: Mepenzolate
indication: Mepenzolate is a postganglionic parasympathetic inhibitor that was previously approved for improving the healing of gastric ulcers, but has been discontinued.

name: Tetrabenazine
indication: Tetrabenazine is a vesicular monoamine transporter 2 (VMAT) inhibitor used for the management of chorea associated with Huntington's Disease.

name: Ixabepilone
indication: Ixabepilone is a microtubule inhibitor administered in combination with capecitabine or alone in the treatment of metastatic or locally advanced breast cancer that has shown inadequate response to taxanes and anthracyclines.

name: Celiprolol
indication: Celiprolol is a beta-blocker for the management of hypertension and angina pectoris.

name: Roxadustat
indication: Roxadustat is a hypoxia-inducible factor (HIF) prolyl hydroxylase inhibitor used to treat symptomatic anemia associated with chronic kidney disease.

name: Febuxostat
indication: Febuxostat is a xanthine oxidase inhibitor used for the management of chronic hyperuricemia in adults with gout who have an inadequate response or intolerance to allopurinol.

name: Dronedarone
indication: Dronedarone is an antiarrhythmic agent used in the reduce the risk of hospitalization in patients with paroxysmal or persistent atrial fibrillation.

name: Nebivolol
indication: Nebivolol is a beta blocking agent used to treat hypertension and aid in the management of heart failure.

name: Huperzine A
indication: Investigated for use/treatment in alzheimer's disease

name: Omacetaxine mepesuccinate
indication: Omacetaxine mepesuccinate is a cephalotaxine used in the treatment of Chronic Myeloid Leukemia (CML) that is intolerant to or resistant to two or more tyrosine kinase inhibitors.

name: Halofuginone
indication: For the treatment of scleroderma, cancer, and restenosis

name: Nilotinib
indication: Nilotinib is a kinase inhibitor used for the chronic phase treatment of Chronic Myeloid Leukemia (CML) that is Philadelphia chromosome positive and for the treatment of CML that is resistant to therapy containing imatinib.

name: Lorcaserin
indication: Lorcaserin is a serotonin 2C receptor agonist used in conjunction with physical activity and calorie restriction for weight loss in obese patients with a body mass index (BMI) of 30 and above, and in overweight patients with weight-related comorbidities.

name: Vildagliptin
indication: Vildagliptin is a once-daily dipeptidyl peptidase 4 (DPP-4) inhibitor used in the management of type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Enoximone
indication: Enoximone is a selective phosphodiesterase inhibitor indicated in the short term treatment of congestive heart failure.

name: Bepotastine
indication: Bepotastine is an ophthalmic H1 antagonist used to treat itchiness associated with allergic conjunctivitis.

name: Milnacipran
indication: Milnacipran is a selective serotonin and norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI) used for the treatment of fibromyalgia and a short-term treatment of major depressive disorder.

name: Ximelagatran
indication: For the treatment of acute deep vein thrombosis

name: Flibanserin
indication: Flibanserin is a 5-HT receptor modulator used for the treatment of selected premenopausal women with acquired, generalized hypoactive sexual desire disorder (HSDD).

name: Oxibendazole
indication: Investigated for use/treatment in infectious and parasitic disease (unspecified) and pediatric indications

name: Oritavancin
indication: Oritavancin is an antibacterial agent used to treat acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections caused by susceptible Gram-positive bacteria.

name: Ceftobiprole
indication: Ceftobiprole is a cephalosporin antibiotic used to treat both community and hospital-acquired pneumonia caused by susceptible bacteria.

name: Clevidipine
indication: Clevidipine is a dihydropyridine L-type calcium channel blocker used to lower blood pressure when oral antihypertensive therapy is not feasible or not desirable.

name: Permethrin
indication: Permethrin is an insecticide used to prevent infestation with Sarcoptes scabiei (scabies).

name: Afamelanotide
indication: Afamelanotide is an injectable subcutaneous implant used to mitigate phototoxicity secondary to erythropoietic protoporphyria (EPP).

name: Ospemifene
indication: Ospemifene is a non-hormonal estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) used to treat moderate to severe dyspareunia, a symptom of vulvar and vaginal atrophy, due to menopause.

name: Iloperidone
indication: Iloperidone is an atypical antipsychotic agent used for the acute treatment of schizophrenia in adults.

name: Lofexidine
indication: Lofexidine is a centrally acting alpha2-adrenergic agonist used for the symptomatic treatment of acute opioid withdrawal syndrome to facilitate abrupt opioid discontinuation in adults.

name: Pirfenidone
indication: Pirfenidone is an agent used for the treatment of idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF).

name: Ezogabine
indication: Ezogabine is an antiepileptic agent used as an adjuvant treatment of partial-onset seizures.

name: Ingenol mebutate
indication: Ingenol mebutate is a topical agent used for the treatment of actinic keratosis.

name: Belinostat
indication: Belinostat is a histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitor used for the treatment of patients with relapsed or refractory peripheral T-cell lymphoma (PTCL).

name: Ataluren
indication: Ataluren is a medication used for the treatment of Duchenne muscular dystrophy.

name: Migalastat
indication: Migalastat is an alpha-galactosidase A chaperone used for the treatment of Fabry disease in patients with an amenable galactosidase alpha gene (GLA) variant.

name: Indacaterol
indication: Indacaterol is an inhaled long-acting beta-2 adrenergic agonist used to relax bronchial smooth muscle and improve symptoms and airflow obstruction caused by Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) and moderate to severe asthma.

name: Erdosteine
indication: Erdosteine is a mucolytic agent used to treat conditions characterized by pathological mucus such as respiratory tract infections and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

name: Ganaxolone
indication: Ganaxolone is a neuroactive steroid GABA-A receptor modulator used for the treatment of seizures associated with CDKL5 deficiency disorder (CDD).

name: Trabectedin
indication: Trabectedin is an alkylating agent approved for the treatment of unresectable or metastatic soft tissue sarcoma (liposarcoma or leiomyosarcoma).

name: Pretomanid
indication: Pretomanid is part of a three-drug regimen used for the treatment of extensively drug-resistant and multidrug-resistant pulmonary tuberculosis.

name: Crisaborole
indication: Crisaborole is a non-steroidal topical medication used for the treatment of mild-moderate atopic dermatitis.

name: Cobimetinib
indication: Cobimetinib is an antineoplastic agent and selective inhibitor of the mitogen-activated extracellular kinase (MEK) pathway used to treat unresectable or metastatic melanoma.

name: Silver sulfadiazine
indication: Silver sulfadiazine is a topical sulfonamide antibiotic that acts on the bacterial cell wall and cell membrane; approved for the treatment of burns.

name: Methsuximide
indication: Methsuximide is a succinimide anticonvulsant that increases the seizure threshold. Primarily used for childhood absence seizures. Functions by suppressing paroxysmal spike-and-wave patterns associated with lapses of consciousness in absence seizures.

name: Gallium nitrate
indication: Gallium nitrate is a medication indicated for cancer-related hypercalcemia.

name: Rotigotine
indication: Rotigotine is a non-selective dopamine agonist used for the treatment of Parkinson's Disease and Restless Leg Syndrome.

name: Samarium (153Sm) lexidronam
indication: Samarium (153Sm) lexidronam is a chelated complex of samarium isotope and EDTMP that concentrates in areas with high bone turnover such as sites of metastases to relieve pain associated with osteoblastic metastatic bone lesions.

name: Vandetanib
indication: Vandetanib is an antineoplastic kinase inhibitor used to treat symptomatic or progressive medullary thyroid cancer in patients with unresectable locally advanced or metastatic disease.

name: Pimavanserin
indication: Pimavanserin is a second generation atypical antipsychotic used for the treatment of hallucinations and delusions caused by Parkinson's Disease.

name: Dexlansoprazole
indication: Dexlansoprazole is a proton pump inhibitor used to help gastrointestinal ulcers heal, to treat symptoms of gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD), to eradicate Helicobacter pylori, and to treat hypersecretory conditions such as Zollinger-Ellison Syndrome.

name: Histamine
indication: Histamine is an ingredient of topical drugs for the relief of joint pain or muscle aches and pains.

name: Iodine
indication: Iodine is an ingredient of nutritional supplements that is also used for disinfection.

name: Tetrachlorodecaoxide
indication: Investigated for use/treatment in acquired immune deficiency syndrome (AIDS) and aids-related infections, cancer/tumors (unspecified), HIV infection, and inflammatory disorders (unspecified)

name: Palovarotene
indication: Palovarotene is a selective agonist of retinoic acid receptor gamma (RARγ) used to reduce heterotopic ossification in patients with Fibrodysplasia Ossificans Progressiva (FOP).

name: Telaprevir
indication: Telaprevir is an NS3/4A viral protease inhibitor used in combination with other antivirals for the curative treatment of chronic Hepatitis C Virus infections.

name: Brivaracetam
indication: Brivaracetam is an anticonvulsant used for the treatment of partial-onset seizures that functions by binding to synaptic vesicle glycoprotein 2A (SV2A) in the brain.

name: Sodium stibogluconate
indication: For the treatment of various types of a protozoal infection called leishmaniasis, which may result from sandfly bites in tropical and temperate parts of the world

name: Levoketoconazole
indication: Levoketoconazole is one of two enantiomeric forms of racemic ketoconazole that strongly inhibits multiple steroidogenic enzymes and is used for the symptomatic treatment of endogenous Cushing's syndrome.

name: Apremilast
indication: Apremilast is a non-steroidal medication used for the treatment of inflammatory conditions such as psoriasis and psoriatic arthritis.

name: Abiraterone
indication: Abiraterone is an antiandrogen used in the treatment of prostate cancer.

name: Obeticholic acid
indication: Obeticholic acid is a bile acid analog and farnesoid X receptor agonist used to treat primary biliary cholangitis in adult patients with inadequate clinical response or intolerance to UDCA.

name: Cariprazine
indication: Cariprazine is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat schizophrenia and acute manic or mixed episodes due to bipolar I disorder.

name: Lumateperone
indication: Lumateperone is a novel 2nd generation antipsychotic used to manage both positive and negative symptoms in patients with schizophrenia.

name: Tapinarof
indication: Tapinarof is a therapeutic aryl hydrocarbon receptor-modulating agent (TAMA) indicated for the treatment of adult psoriasis.

name: Cenobamate
indication: Cenobamate is a small molecule drug indicated to treat partial onset seizures in adults.

name: Tirbanibulin
indication: Tirbanibulin is a tyrosine kinase and tubulin inhibitor used to treat actinic keratosis on the face or scalp.

name: Sertindole
indication: Sertindole is an atypical antipsychotic indicated in the treatment of schizophrenia.

name: Spiramycin
indication: Spiramycin is a macrolide antimicrobial agent used in the treatment of various bacterial infections.

name: Sulfathiazole
indication: Sulfathiazole is effective against a wide range of gram positive and gram negative pathogenic microorganisms

name: Mianserin
indication: Mianserin is a tetracyclic antidepressant with therapeutic activity similar to amitriptyline used to treat depression and anxiety.

name: Teicoplanin
indication: Teicoplanin is a glycopeptide antibiotic with a similar mechanism of action and spectrum of activity to vancomycin used to treat various infections caused by gram-positive bacteria.

name: Sulfadimethoxine
indication: For use in the treatment of infections

name: Acetylcysteine
indication: Acetylcysteine is a medication that can be used as a mucolytic in patients with certain lung conditions and as an antidote for acetaminophen overdose.

name: Nylidrin
indication: Nylidrin is a vasodilator used to treat patients with peripheral vascular disorders, and elderly patients with symptoms associated with organic mental disorders.

name: Pizotifen
indication: Pizotifen is a serotonin and tryptamine antagonist indicated for migraine prophylaxis.

name: Pentaerythritol tetranitrate
indication: Used for the treatment of angina pectoris [L2393]

name: Rimonabant
indication: For use in conjunction with diet and exercise for patients with a body mass index greater than 30 kg/m<sup>2</sup>, or patients wih a BMI greater than 27 kg/m<sup>2</sup> with associated risk factors, such as type 2 diabetes or dyslipidaemia

name: Noscapine
indication: Noscapine is a non-sedating isoquinoline alkaloid used primarily for its antitussive properties.

name: Romidepsin
indication: Romidepsin is a histone deacetylase (HDAC) inhibitor used to treat cutaneous T-cell lymphoma.

name: Pixantrone
indication: Pixantrone is an antineoplastic agent use to treat patients with relapsed or refractory aggressive Non-Hodgkin B-cell Lymphomas (NHL).

name: Icatibant
indication: Icatibant is a bradykinin B2 receptor antagonist used to treat acute episodes of swelling and inflammation associated with hereditary angioedema (HAE).

name: Rufinamide
indication: Rufinamide is an antiepileptic drug used as adjunctive therapy to treat seizures associated with Lennox-Gastaut Syndrome (LGS).

name: Lasofoxifene
indication: Investigated for use/treatment in postmenopausal osteoporosis to reduce the risk of both vertebral and novertebral fractures, as well as address other postmenopausal conditions, including reduction in risk of breast cancer and treatment of vulvar and vaginal atrophy (VVA)

name: Alogliptin
indication: Alogliptin is a dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-4) inhibitor used to treat hyperglycemia in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Tapentadol
indication: Tapentadol is an opioid used to manage severe pain that has not responded to non-opioid medications, and for which opioid analgesic therapy is appropriate.

name: Sugammadex
indication: Sugammadex is a modified gamma cyclodextrin used to reverse neuromuscular blockade induced by vecuronium bromide and rocuronium bromide which are agents used for anesthesia.

name: Silodosin
indication: Silodosin is an alpha-1 adrenergic receptor antagonist used to treat symptoms associated with benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH).

name: Prasugrel
indication: Prasugrel is a P2Y12 platelet inhibitor used to reduce risk of thrombotic cardiovascular events in unstable angina or non-ST-elevation myocardial infarction (NSTEMI), and in patients with STEMI when managed with either primary or delayed PCI.

name: Eltrombopag
indication: Eltrombopag is a thrombopoietin receptor agonist used to treat thrombocytopenia or aplastic anemia associated with various etiologies.

name: Doripenem
indication: Doripenem is an antibiotic of the penem class used to treat complicated intra-abdominal and urinary tract infections.

name: Tolvaptan
indication: Tolvaptan is a selective vasopressin V2-receptor antagonist to slow kidney function decline in patients at risk for rapidly progressing autosomal dominant polycystic kidney disease (ADPKD). Also used to treat hypervolemic and euvolemic hyponatremia.

name: Regadenoson
indication: Regadenoson is a coronary vasodilator used in radionuclide myocardial perfusion imaging (MPI).

name: Ferumoxytol
indication: Ferumoxytol is an intravenous iron replacement product used to treat iron deficiency anemia (IDA) in patients with chronic kidney disease (CKD), or in patients who are unable to tolerate or who have not responded adequately to oral iron supplementation.

name: Asenapine
indication: Asenapine is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat patients with bipolar I disorder and patients with schizophrenia.

name: Vernakalant
indication: Vernakalant is an antiarrhythmic medication used to treat patients with atrial fibrillation.

name: Lacosamide
indication: Lacosamide is an antiepileptic drug used to treat partial onset seizures in adults.

name: Rivaroxaban
indication: Rivaroxaban is a factor Xa inhibitor used to treat deep vein thrombosis (DVT) and pulmonary embolism (PE). May also be used as thrombosis prophylaxis in specific situations.

name: Nalmefene
indication: Nalmefene is an opioid antagonist used to reduce alcohol consumption in adults with alcohol dependence and treat and prevent opioid overdose.

name: Maribavir
indication: Maribavir is a cytomegalovirus (CMV) pUL97 kinase inhibitor used for the treatment of refractory post-transplant CMV infection.

name: Avanafil
indication: Avanafil is a phosphodiesterase-5 (PDE5) inhibitor used to treat erectile dysfunction.

name: Eflornithine
indication: Eflornithine is a medication used topically to reduce unwanted facial hair growth in women. The postulated mechanism of action is through irreversible inhibition of ornithine decarboxylase (ODC) in the skin.

name: Arzoxifene
indication: Investigated for use/treatment in breast cancer, osteoporosis, and endometrial cancer

name: Hexaminolevulinate
indication: Hexaminolevulinate is an optical imaging agent used to perform Blue Light Cystoscopy (BLC™) in order to detect carcinoma of the bladder.

name: Droxidopa
indication: Droxidopa is a medication used to treat symptomatic neurogenic orthostatic hypotension (nOH) caused by dopamine beta-hydroxylase deficiency, non-diabetic autonomic neuropathy and primary autonomic failure caused by conditions such as Parkinson's disease.

name: Udenafil
indication: Udenafil is a PDE5 inhibitor used to treat erectile dysfunction.

name: Sitaxentan
indication: Investigated for use/treatment in pulmonary hypertension, connective tissue diseases, hypertension, and congestive heart failure

name: Alvimopan
indication: Alvimopan is an opioid antagonist used to reduce healing time of the upper and lower gastrointestinal tract following surgical procedures that involve bowel resection with primary anastomosis.

name: Levocetirizine
indication: Levocetirizine is an H1-receptor antagonist used to treat symptoms associated with chronic allergic rhinitis and uncomplicated cases of chronic idiopathic urticaria.

name: Ziconotide
indication: Ziconotide is an N-type calcium channel antagonist used to manage patients with severe chronic pain who cannot tolerate, or who have not responded adequately to other treatments such as intrathecal morphine and systemic analgesics.

name: Temsirolimus
indication: Temsirolimus is a antineoplastic agent used in the treatment of renal cell carcinoma (RCC) that works by inhibiting mTOR.

name: Amisulpride
indication: Amisulpride is a dopamine D2 receptor antagonist used in the treatment of acute and chronic schizophrenia, and in the prevention and treatment of postoperative nausea and vomiting in adults.

name: Simeprevir
indication: Simeprevir is a direct-acting antiviral agent that inhibits HCV NS3/4A protease to treat chronic hepatitis C virus (HCV) infection in adults with HCV genotype 1 or 4.

name: Dapagliflozin
indication: Dapagliflozin is a sodium-glucose cotransporter 2 inhibitor used in the management of type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Saxagliptin
indication: Saxagliptin is an DPP-4 inhibitor used for the management of type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Bazedoxifene
indication: Bazedoxifene is a selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM) used to treat moderate to severe vasomotor symptoms in menopause and osteoporosis alone or in combination with conjugated estrogens.

name: Telavancin
indication: Telavancin is an antibacterial agent used in the treatment of complicated skin and skin structure infections and types of hospital-acquired bacterial pneumonia.

name: Ambrisentan
indication: Ambrisentan is a selective type A endothelin receptor antagonist used to treat primary pulmonary arterial hypertension and pulmonary arterial hypertension based on diagnostic classifications.

name: Doxercalciferol
indication: Doxercalciferol is a synthetic vitamin D2 analog used to treat secondary hyperparathyroidism in patients with chronic kidney disease with or without therapy of dialysis.

name: Oxymetholone
indication: Oxymetholone is an anabolic steroid used for the treatment of types of anemia, such as acquired aplastic anemia, congenital aplastic anemia, myelofibrosis, and the hypoplastic anemias.

name: Armodafinil
indication: Armodafinil is a stimulant used to improve wakefulness in adult patients with excessive sleepiness associated with obstructive sleep apnea, narcolepsy, or shift work disorder.

name: Etravirine
indication: Etravirine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used in the treatment of HIV-1 infections in combination with other antiretroviral agents.

name: Cangrelor
indication: Cangrelor is a P2Y12 platelet receptor antagonist used during percutaneous coronary intervention to reduce the risk for periprocedural myocardial infarction (MI), repeat coronary revascularization, and stent thrombosis (ST).

name: Lonafarnib
indication: Lonafarnib is a potent farnesyl transferase inhibitor used to reduce mortality associated with Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome (HGPS) and other progeroid laminopathies.

name: Prucalopride
indication: Prucalopride is a 5-HT4 receptor agonist indicated to treat adults with chronic idiopathic constipation.

name: Pazopanib
indication: Pazopanib is an antineoplastic agent used in the treatment of advanced renal cell cancer and advanced soft tissue sarcoma in patients with prior chemotherapy.

name: Ceftaroline fosamil
indication: Ceftaroline fosamil is an antibacterial agent used to treat various bacterial infections, such as acute bacterial skin and skin structure infections and community-acquired bacterial pneumonia.

name: Agomelatine
indication: Agomelatine is indicated to treat major depressive episodes in adults

name: Midostaurin
indication: Midostaurin is an antineoplastic agent used to treat high-risk acute myeloid leukemia (AML) with specific mutations, aggressive systemic mastocytosis (ASM), systemic mastocytosis with associated hematologic neoplasm (SM-AHN), or mast cell leukemia (MCL).

name: Panobinostat
indication: Panobinostat is a non-selective histone deacetylase inhibitor used to treat multiple myeloma in combination with other antineoplastic agents.

name: Apixaban
indication: Apixaban is an anticoagulant used for the prophylaxis of stroke and systemic embolism in nonvalvular atrial fibrillation, and deep vein thrombosis(DVT) leading to pulmonary embolism(PE), including in patients after a hip or knee replacement surgery.

name: Tafenoquine
indication: Tafenoquine is an antiparasitic agent used for the treatment and prevention of relapse of Vivax malaria.

name: Peramivir
indication: Peramivir is an intravenous antiviral agent used to treat acute uncomplicated influenza in patients aged 2 years and older who are shown to be symptomatic for no more than two days.

name: Bosutinib
indication: Bosutinib is an antineoplastic agent used for the treatment of chronic, accelerated, or blast phase Philadelphia chromosome-positive (Ph+) chronic myelogenous leukemia (CML) in adults with inadequate clinical response to other treatments.

name: Axitinib
indication: Axitinib is an oral VEGFR and kinase inhibitor used for the treatment of advanced renal cell carcinoma after failure of one prior systemic therapy.

name: Isavuconazonium
indication: Isavuconazonium is a triazole antifungal used for the treatment of invasive aspergillosis and mucormycosis.

name: Dalfampridine
indication: Dalfampridine is a potassium channel blocker used for the improvement of motor function in patients with multiple sclerosis (MS).

name: Safinamide
indication: Safinamide is a MAO-B inhibitor used as an add-on treatment to levodopa/carbidopa for Parkinson's disease during "off" episodes.

name: Pasireotide
indication: Pasireotide is a somatostatin analog used in the treatment of Cushing’s disease, specifically for those patients whom pituitary surgery is not appropriate.

name: Vilazodone
indication: Vilazodone is an antidepressant agent used for the treatment of major depressive disorder that targets the 5-HT transporter and 5-HT1A receptors.

name: Ethanolamine oleate
indication: Ethanolamine oleate is a mild sclerosing agent used in the treatment of esophageal varices with recent bleeding episodes.

name: Mepyramine
indication: Mepyramine is an antihistamine agent used for the symptomatic treatment of allergy, hypersensitivity reactions, and pruritic skin disorders.

name: Xylometazoline
indication: Xylometazoline is a direct-acting alpha-adrenergic agonist used for the symptomatic treatment of nasal congestion and minor inflammation due to allergies or colds.

name: Dabigatran etexilate
indication: Dabigatran etexilate is an anticoagulant used for the prevention of venous thromboembolic events or stroke in patients with recent elective hip or knee replacement surgery and atrial fibrillation.

name: Artemether
indication: Artemether is an antimalarial agent used in combination with lumefantrine for the treatment of acute uncomplicated malaria caused by Plasmodium falciparum.

name: Betahistine
indication: Betahistine is an antivertigo agent used for the reduction of episodes of vertigo association with Ménière's disease.

name: Degarelix
indication: Degarelix is a GnRH receptor antagonist used in the management of advanced prostate cancer.

name: Desvenlafaxine
indication: Desvenlafaxine is an antidepressant agent and SNRI used for the treatment of major depressive disorders in adults.

name: Dexmethylphenidate
indication: Dexmethylphenidate is a norepinephrine-dopamine reuptake inhibitor used in the treatment of ADHD in conjunction with other therapies.

name: Fesoterodine
indication: Fesoterodine is an antimuscarinic agent used in the treatment of overactive bladder with symptoms of urge urinary incontinence, urgency, and frequency.

name: Gadobutrol
indication: Gadobutrol is a contrast agent used during diagnostic procedures to visualize disrupted areas of blood brain barrier (BBB) and/or abnormal vascularity of the central nervous system.

name: Iobenguane
indication: Iobenguane is a radiopharmaceutical agent used for the diagnosis of primary and metastatic pheochromocytoma or neuroblastoma.

name: Gadofosveset trisodium
indication: Gadofosveset trisodium is an intravenous contrast agent used during magnetic resonance angiography (MRA) to evaluate aortoiliac occlusive disease (AIOD) in adults with peripheral vascular disease.

name: Isometheptene
indication: Isometheptene is a sympathomimetic used to relieve painful spasms in combination with other agents such as caffeine and metamizole.

name: Levonordefrin
indication: Levonordefrin is a topical sympathomimetic amine found in local anesthetic products that is used for nasal decongestion or vasoconstriction during dental procedures.

name: Lumefantrine
indication: Lumefantrine is an antimalarial agent used in combination with artemether for the treatment of acute uncomplicated malaria caused by Plasmodium falciparum.

name: Methacholine
indication: Methacholine is a parasympathomimetic bronchoconstrictor used to diagnose bronchial hyperreactivity in subjects who do not have clinically apparent asthma.

name: Methyltestosterone
indication: Methyltestosterone is a synthetic anabolic steroid used for the replacement therapy in conditions associated with testosterone deficiencies in males, such as hypogonadism, and treatment of advancing inoperable metastatic breast cancer in females.

name: Naphazoline
indication: Naphazoline is a sympathomimetic vasoconstrictor used for the symptomatic relief of redness and itching of the eye, and nasal congestion.

name: Nilvadipine
indication: Nilvadipine is a calcium channel blocker used to manage arterial hypertension.

name: Norelgestromin
indication: Norelgestromin is a progestin used for the prevention of pregnancy in women who elect to use a transdermal patch as a method of contraception.

name: Propylhexedrine
indication: It is used to provide temporary symptomatic relief of nasal congestion due to colds, allergies and allergic rhinitis

name: Potassium Iodide
indication: Potassium Iodide is an oral antithyroid agent used for the prevention of radioactive iodine uptake into the thyroid gland during a nuclear radiation emergency.

name: Fospropofol
indication: Fospropofol is a sedative-­hypnotic agent indicated for monitored anesthesia care (MAC) sedation in adult patients undergoing diagnostic or therapeutic procedures.

name: Fosaprepitant
indication: Fosaprepitant is an antiemetic drug used in combination with other antiemetic agents for the prevention of acute and delayed nausea and vomiting caused by chemotherapy.

name: Stanozolol
indication: Stanozolol is an anabolic steroid used to manage hereditary angioedema.

name: Buserelin
indication: Buserelin is a LHRH agonist used for the palliative treatment of hormone-dependent advanced carcinoma of the prostate gland in males and treatment of endometriosis in females.

name: Aluminum hydroxide
indication: Aluminum hydroxide is an antacid used for the symptomatic relief of heartburn, acid indigestion, and sour stomach.

name: Calcium carbonate
indication: Calcium carbonate is an ionic compound used as a calcium supplement or antacid used for the symptomatic relief of heartburn, acid indigestion, and sour stomach.

name: Lornoxicam
indication: Lornoxicam is an NSAID indicated in the treatment of mild to moderate pain, as well as rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis.

name: Sulfaphenazole
indication: For the treatment bacterial infections

name: Aceclofenac
indication: Aceclofenac is indicated for the relief of pain and inflammation in osteoarthritis, rheumatoid arthritis and ankylosing spondylitis

name: Ambroxol
indication: Ambroxol is a medication indicated for airway secretion clearance therapy.

name: Drotaverine
indication: Drotaverine is a phosphodiesterase-4 inhibitor used to alleviate gastrointestinal and genitourinary smooth muscle spasms.

name: Beta carotene
indication: Beta carotene is a vitamin A precursor found in various nutritional supplements and health products.

name: Betaine
indication: Betaine is a methyl group donor used for the treatment of homocystinuria to decrease elevated homocysteine blood levels.

name: Manganese
indication: Manganese is a transition metal used for supplementation of manganese during Total Parenteral Nutrition (TPN).

name: Tetryzoline
indication: Tetryzoline is an alpha-adrenergic agonist used in the temporary symptomatic relief of discomfort and redness of the eyes due to minor irritations, as well as alleviate nasal congestion.

name: Alcaftadine
indication: Alcaftadine is a H1 histamine receptor antagonist for ophthalmic use to prevent itching associated with allergic conjunctivitis.

name: Ammonium lactate
indication: Ammonium lactate is an inorganic compound used for the symptomatic treatment of dry, scaly skin (xerosis) and ichthyosis vulgaris and for temporary relief of itching associated with these conditions.

name: Bendamustine
indication: Bendamustine is an antineoplastic agent used for the treatment of chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL) and indolent B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma (NHL) that has progressed following rituximab therapy.

name: Benzyl alcohol
indication: Benzyl alcohol is an antiparasitic agent used for the topical treatment of head lice infestation in patients 6 months of age and older.

name: Besifloxacin
indication: Besifloxacin is a fluoroquinolone antibiotic agent used for the treatment of bacterial conjunctivitis.

name: Cabazitaxel
indication: Cabazitaxel is an antineoplastic agent used for the treatment of hormone-refractory metastatic prostate cancer previously treated with a docetaxel-containing treatment regimen.

name: Capsaicin
indication: Capsaicin is a topical analgesic agent used for the symptomatic relief of neuropathic pain associated with post-herpetic neuralgia, as well as other muscle and joint pain.

name: Carglumic acid
indication: Carglumic acid is an analog of N-acetylglutamate (NAG) used for the treatment of acute and chronic hyperammonemia in patients with N-acetylglutamate synthase (NAGS) deficiency.

name: Chenodeoxycholic acid
indication: Chenodeoxycholic acid is a bile acid used for the treatment of primary biliary cirrhosis.

name: Cupric sulfate
indication: Cupric sulfate is a compound used as an intravenous copper supplement for Total Parenteral Nutrition (TPN).

name: Difluprednate
indication: Difluprednate is a topical corticosteroid used for the symptomatic treatment of inflammation and pain associated with ocular surgery.

name: Dimercaprol
indication: Dimercaprol is a chelating agent used as an antidote to arsenic, gold, and mercury poisoning, as well as acute lead poisoning in combination with edetate calcium disodium.

name: Prussian blue
indication: Prussian blue is a chelating agent used to reduce the extent of systemic contamination with radioactive cesium and/or radioactive or non-radioactive thallium.

name: Gallium citrate Ga-67
indication: Gallium citrate Ga-67 is a radiopharmaceutical agent used in the detection of the presence and extent of Hodgkin's disease, lymphoma, and bronchogenic carcinoma, as well as some acute inflammatory lesions.

name: Ganirelix
indication: Ganirelix is a GnRH antagonist used in assisted reproduction in women undergoing controlled ovarian hyperstimulation to control ovulation by inhibiting the premature LH surges.

name: Halcinonide
indication: Halcinonide is a corticosteroid used for the management and symptomatic relief of the inflammatory and pruritic manifestations of corticosteroid-responsive dermatoses.

name: Hexocyclium
indication: The World Health Organization classifies hexocyclium as a drug for functional gastrointestinal disorders [L876]

name: Histrelin
indication: Histrelin is a GnRH agonist found in subcutaneous implants used for the treatment of pediatric patients with central precocious puberty and the palliative treatment of advanced prostate cancer.

name: Hydroxyprogesterone caproate
indication: Hydroxyprogesterone caproate is a synthetic progestin used for the prevention of spontaneous preterm births in singleton pregnancies in women who have previously had a spontaneous preterm birth.

name: Lanreotide
indication: Lanreotide is a somatostatin analog used for the treatment of unresectable, well- or moderately-differentiated, locally advanced or metastatic gastroenteropancreatic neuroendocrine tumors and acromegaly.

name: Lanthanum carbonate
indication: Lanthanum carbonate is a phosphate binder indicated for the reduction of serum phosphate in patients with end stage renal disease.

name: Lodoxamide
indication: Lodoxamide is an ophthalmic agent used for the treatment of the ocular disorders referred to by the terms vernal keratoconjunctivitis, vernal conjunctivitis, and vernal keratitis.

name: Mafenide
indication: Mafenide is an antimicrobial topical agent indicated for use as an adjunctive treatment to control bacterial infection when used under moist dressings over meshed autografts on excised burn wounds.

name: Mangafodipir
indication: Mangafodipir is an organ-specific paramagnetic contrast agent indicated for the imaging of the hepatobiliary system and detecting lesions in the liver and pancreas.

name: Methenamine
indication: Methenamine is a urinary tract antiseptic and antibacterial drug used for the prophylaxis and treatment of frequently recurring urinary tract infections requiring a long-term therapy.

name: Methylnaltrexone
indication: Methylnaltrexone is a μ-opioid antagonist used for the treatment of opioid-induced constipation in palliative patients that are inadequately responding to laxative therapy.

name: Nepafenac
indication: Nepafenac is an ophthalmic NSAID used for the symptomatic treatment of pain and inflammation associated with cataract surgery.

name: Niclosamide
indication: Niclosamide is an anthelmintic indicated in the treatment of beef, pork, fish, and dwarf tapeworm infections in adults and children.

name: Nonoxynol-9
indication: Nonoxynol-9 is a vaginal spermicide used for the non-hormonal contraception in conjunction with other modes of contraception.

name: Plerixafor
indication: Plerixafor is a selective chemokine receptor (CXCR4) antagonist used with filgrastim to mobilize hematopoietic stem cells to the peripheral blood for collection and autologous transplantation in patients with non-Hodgkin’s lymphoma (NHL) and multiple myeloma (MM).

name: Plicamycin
indication: For the treatment of testicular cancer, as well as hypercalcemia and hypercalciuria associated with a variety of advanced forms of cancer

name: Polidocanol
indication: Polidocanol is a sclerosing agent used for the treatment of uncomplicated spider veins and uncomplicated reticular veins, all less than 3 mm in diameter, in the lower extremity.

name: Pralatrexate
indication: Pralatrexate is an antineoplastic agent used for the treatment of relapsed or refractory peripheral T-cell lymphoma.

name: Pyrithione
indication: Pyrithione is an antimicrobial agent used for the treatment of dandruff and seborrheic dermatitis.

name: Pyrvinium
indication: Pyrvinium is an anthelmintic agent used for the treatment of pinworm infestations.

name: Raltegravir
indication: Raltegravir is an antiretroviral agent used for the treatment of HIV infections in conjunction with other antiretrovirals.

name: Phenylbutyric acid
indication: Phenylbutyric acid is an agent indicated for the adjunctive therapy for the management of chronic urea cycle disorders due to deficiencies in specific enzymes, including the neonatal-onset deficiency and late-onset disease with a history of hyperammonemic encephalopathy.

name: Sulconazole
indication: Sulconazole is a topical antifungal agent used for the treatment of tinea cruris, tinea corporis, and tinea versicolor caused by susceptible fungal strains.

name: Tiopronin
indication: Tiopronin is a thiol agent indicated for the prevention of kidney stone formation in patients with severe homozygous cystinuria.

name: Triethylenetetramine
indication: Triethylenetetramine is a copper chelating agent used for the management of Wilson's disease in cases where penicillamine therapy is clinically inappropriate.

name: Triptorelin
indication: Triptorelin is a GnRH agonist indicated for the palliative treatment of advanced prostate cancer.

name: Unoprostone
indication: Unoprostone is a prostaglandin analogue used to lower intraocular pressure in patients with open-angle glaucoma or ocular hypertension who are clinically unresponsive to other ocular antihypertensive agents.

name: Viomycin
indication: Viomycin is an essential component in the drug cocktail currently used to fight infections of Mycobacterium tuberculosis

name: Chloramphenicol succinate
indication: Chloramphenicol succinate is a broad-spectrum antibiotic agent used for the treatment of acute and severe infections caused by susceptible bacterial strains.

name: Parecoxib
indication: Parecoxib is a selective COX-2 inhibitor and NSAID used for the short-term management of perioperative pain.

name: Triclosan
indication: Triclosan is an antimicrobial agent in clinical setting for disinfection, and prevention of spread and growth of bacteria, fungus, and mildew.

name: Antazoline
indication: Antazoline is an antihistamine agent used for the symptomatic treatment of nasal congestion and allergic conjunctivitis.

name: Dimetindene
indication: Dimetindene is a 1st generation selective H1 antagonist used topically as an antipruritic and orally to treat allergies.

name: Nandrolone decanoate
indication: Nandrolone decanoate is an anabolic steroid indicated for the management of the anemia of renal insufficiency by increasing hemoglobin and red cell mass.

name: Triflusal
indication: Triflusal is a medication related to acetylsalicylic acid with antithrombotic effects used in the treatment of thromboembolic diseases.

name: Lurasidone
indication: Lurasidone is an atypical antipsychotic used to treat schizophrenia and depressive episodes associated with bipolar I disorder.

name: Ticagrelor
indication: Ticagrelor is a P2Y12 platelet inhibitor used in patients with a history of myocardial infarction or with acute coronary syndrome (ACS) to prevent future myocardial infarction, stroke and cardiovascular death.

name: Hyaluronic acid
indication: Hyaluronic acid is a glycosaminoglycan used for the relief of joint pain, wound healing, ophthalmologic treatment, cosmetic treatment, and various other applications.

name: Tafluprost
indication: Tafluprost is an ophthalmic prostaglandin analog used to lower intraocular pressure in patients with ocular hypertension or open-angle glaucoma.

name: Ivacaftor
indication: Ivacaftor is a cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) potentiator used alone or in combination products to treat cystic fibrosis in patients who have specific genetic mutations that are responsive to the medication.

name: Azilsartan medoxomil
indication: Azilsartan medoxomil is an angiotensin II receptor blocker used to treat hypertension alone or in combination with other antihypertensive agents, such as chlorthalidone.

name: Spinosad
indication: Spinosad is a pediculicide used topically to treat head lice.

name: Ioflupane I-123
indication: Ioflupane I-123 is a radiopharmaceutical used in single photon emission computed tomography (SPECT) brain imaging to help diagnose patients with suspected Parkinsonian syndromes.

name: Deferiprone
indication: Deferiprone is an iron chelator used to treat patients with transfusional iron overload caused by thalassemia syndromes.

name: Lomitapide
indication: Lomitapide is a microsomal triglyceride transfer protein inhibitor used to lower cholesterol associated with homozygous familial hypercholesterolemia (HoFH), reducing risk of cardiovascular events such as myocardial infarction and stroke.

name: Vismodegib
indication: Vismodegib is a hedgehog pathway inhibitor used to treat patients with locally advanced or metastatic basal cell carcinoma.

name: Tauroursodeoxycholic acid
indication: Tauroursodeoxycholic acid is the taurine conjugate of ursodeoxycholic acid with antiapoptotic and ER stress response dampening effects used in some countries to treat gallstones. It is also being investigated for a wide variety of other conditions.

name: Acetylcarnitine
indication: Acetylcarnitine is an acetylated form of the amino acid derivative L-carnitine that assists in mitochondrial fatty acid metabolism. It is under investigation as a treatment for numerous conditions, including neuropathy, depression, and dementia.

name: Pitavastatin
indication: Pitavastatin is an HMG-CoA reductase inhibitor used to lower lipid levels and reduce the risk of cardiovascular disease including myocardial infarction and stroke.

name: Rilpivirine
indication: Rilpivirine is a non-nucleoside reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NNRTI) used in combination with other antiretrovirals to specifically treat human immunodeficiency virus type 1 (HIV-1).

name: Crizotinib
indication: Crizotinib is a receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor used to treat metastatic non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) where the tumors have been confirmed to be anaplastic lymphoma kinase (ALK), or ROS1-positive.

name: Ulipristal
indication: Ulipristal is a selective progesterone receptor modulator used for emergency contraception after unprotected intercourse or in a situation where a planned method of contraception has failed.

name: Fingolimod
indication: Fingolimod is a sphingosine 1-phosphate receptor modulator used to treat patients with the relapsing-remitting form of multiple sclerosis (MS) and studied to manage lung complications of COVID-19.

name: Eribulin
indication: Eribulin is a microtubule inhibitor used to treat metastatic breast cancer and metastatic or unresectable liposarcoma.

name: Gabapentin enacarbil
indication: Gabapentin enacarbil is a gabapentin prodrug used to treat Restless Legs Syndrome (RLS) and postherpetic neuralgia (PHN).

name: Boceprevir
indication: Boceprevir is a hepatitis C virus NS3/4A protease inhibitor used in combination with other medications to treat chronic hepatitis C genotype 1 infection. Boceprevir is not indicated as monotherapy.

name: Fidaxomicin
indication: Fidaxomicin is a macrolide antibiotic used to treat diarrhea associated with Clostridium difficile infection.

name: Cabozantinib
indication: Cabozantinib is a tyrosine kinase inhibitor used to treat advanced renal cell carcinoma, hepatocellular carcinoma, and medullary thyroid cancer.

name: Ruxolitinib
indication: Ruxolitinib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat various types of myelofibrosis, polycythemia vera in patients who have not responded to or cannot tolerate hydroxyurea, and to treat graft-versus-host disease in cases that are refractory to steroid treatment.

name: Teriflunomide
indication: Teriflunomide is a pyrimidine synthesis inhibitor with anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory properties used to treat patients with the relapsing-remitting form of multiple sclerosis.

name: Vemurafenib
indication: Vemurafenib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat patients with Erdheim-Chester Disease who have the BRAF V600 mutation, and melanoma in patients who have the BRAF V600E mutation.

name: Linagliptin
indication: Linagliptin is a dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-4) inhibitor used to manage hyperglycemia in patients with type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Perampanel
indication: Perampanel is a non-competitive AMPA glutamate receptor antagonist used to treat partial-onset seizures with or without secondarily generalized seizures, and as adjunctive treatment of primary generalized tonic-clonic seizures in patients with epilepsy.

name: Gadoxetic acid
indication: Gadoxetic acid is a gadolinium-based contrast agent used in magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) to help characterize lesions in the liver.

name: Icosapent ethyl
indication: Icosapent ethyl is an ethyl ester of eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) that reduces synthesis and enhances clearance of triglycerides that is used to treat patients with severe hypertriglyceridemia.

name: Carfilzomib
indication: Carfilzomib is a proteasome inhibitor used either alone or in conjunction with a chemotherapy regimen to treat patients with relapsed or refractory multiple myeloma.

name: Linaclotide
indication: Linaclotide is a guanylate cyclase-C agonist used to treat constipation associated with irritable bowel syndrome or that is idiopathic in nature.

name: Mirabegron
indication: Mirabegron is a beta-3 adrenergic agonist used to treat overactive bladder and neurogenic detrusor overactivity.

name: Tofacitinib
indication: Tofacitinib is a Janus kinase (JAK) inhibitor used to treat rheumatic conditions, such as rheumatoid arthritis and ankylosing spondylitis, and ulcerative colitis.

name: Regorafenib
indication: Regorafenib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat patients with metastatic colorectal cancer, unresectable, locally advanced, or metastatic gastrointestinal stromal tumors, and hepatocellular carcinoma.

name: Aclidinium
indication: Aclidinium is an inhaled long-acting anticholinergic used as a maintenance bronchodilator in patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

name: Enzalutamide
indication: Enzalutamide is a second-generation androgen receptor inhibitor used to treat castration-resistant prostate cancer and metastatic castration-sensitive prostate cancer.

name: Ponatinib
indication: Ponatinib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat patients with various types of chronic myeloid leukemia (CML).

name: Bedaquiline
indication: Bedaquiline is a diarylquinoline antimycobacterial used in combination with other antibacterials to treat pulmonary multidrug resistant tuberculosis (MDR-TB).

name: Formestane
indication: For the treatment of estrogen-receptor positive breast cancer in post-menopausal women

name: Fluticasone furoate
indication: Fluticasone furoate is an inhaled corticosteroid that can be used as maintenance treatment of asthma and/or chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD) depending on the product. Also available as a nasal spray to manage symptoms of allergic rhinitis.

name: Canagliflozin
indication: Canagliflozin is a sodium-glucose co-transporter 2 (SGLT2) inhibitor used to manage hyperglycemia in type 2 diabetes mellitus (DM). Also used to reduce the risk of major cardiovascular events in patients with established cardiovascular disease and type 2 DM.

name: Dimethyl fumarate
indication: Dimethyl fumarate is a medication used to treat patients with the relapsing-remitting form of multiple sclerosis.

name: Glycerol phenylbutyrate
indication: Glycerol phenylbutyrate is a nitrogen-binding agent used to manage patients with urea cycle disorders who cannot be sufficiently managed amino acid supplementation and/or dietary restrictions.

name: Pomalidomide
indication: Pomalidomide is a thalidomide analogue used in combination with dexamethasone to treat patients with multiple myeloma.

name: Trametinib
indication: Trametinib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat patients with specific types of melanoma, non-small cell lung cancer, and thyroid cancer.

name: Dabrafenib
indication: Dabrafenib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat patients with specific types of melanoma, non-small cell lung cancer, and thyroid cancer.

name: Radium Ra 223 dichloride
indication: Radium Ra 223 dichloride is a radiopharmaceutical agent used to treat patients with castration-resistant prostate cancer, symptomatic bone metastases and no known visceral metastatic disease.

name: Afatinib
indication: Afatinib is an antineoplastic agent used for the treatment of locally advanced or metastatic non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) with non-resistant EGFR mutations or resistance to platinum-based chemotherapy.

name: Levomilnacipran
indication: Levomilnacipran is a selective serotonin and norepinephrine reuptake inhibitor (SNRI) used to treat major depressive disorder (MDD).

name: Dolutegravir
indication: Dolutegravir is an antiviral agent used for the treatment of HIV-1 infections in combination with other antiretroviral agents.

name: Riociguat
indication: Riociguat is a stimulator of soluble guanylate cyclase indicated for the management of persistent or recurrent chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension and pulmonary arterial hypertension.

name: Macitentan
indication: Macitentan is an endothelin receptor antagonist used to manage pulmonary arterial hypertension to delay disease progression.

name: Luliconazole
indication: Luliconazole is a topical antifungal agent used to treat fungal infections.

name: Sofosbuvir
indication: Sofosbuvir is a direct-acting antiviral agent used to treat specific hepatitis C virus (HCV) infections in combination with other antiviral agents.

name: Inositol nicotinate
indication: Inositol nicotinate is a vasodilator and source of niacin found in dietary supplements.

name: Gemeprost
indication: Gemeprost is a prostaglandin E1 analogue used for cervical dilation and, in combination with mifepristone, for pregnancy termination.

name: Diosmin
indication: Diosmin is a citrus flavonoid medication used to support vascular health.

name: Bromhexine
indication: Bromhexine is a mucolytic drug used to decrease the viscosity of mucus in the airway, enhancing mucus clearance.

name: Bisacodyl
indication: Bisacodyl is a stimulant laxative used for the temporary relief of occasional constipation and cleansing of the colon as a preparation for colonoscopy in adults.

name: Aliskiren
indication: Aliskiren is a direct renin inhibitor used to manage hypertension.

name: Ledipasvir
indication: Ledipasvir is a direct-acting antiviral agent used to treat specific hepatitis C virus (HCV) infections in combination with other antiviral agents.

name: Vorapaxar
indication: Vorapaxar is a platelet aggregation inhibitor used to reduce thrombotic cardiovascular events in patients with a history of myocardial infarction (MI) or peripheral arterial disease (PAD).

name: Miltefosine
indication: Miltefosine is an antileishmanial agent used to treat leishmaniasis, a group of disease caused by parasites of the Leishmania type.

name: Suvorexant
indication: Suvorexant is a orexin receptor antagonist used to treat insomnia that is characterized by difficulties with sleep onset and/or sleep maintenance.

name: Empagliflozin
indication: Empagliflozin is an SGLT2 inhibitor used to manage type 2 diabetes mellitus.

name: Eliglustat
indication: Eliglustat is a glucosylceramide synthase used to treat type 1 Gaucher disease in patients who are CYP2D6 extensive, intermediate, or poor metabolizers.

name: Efinaconazole
indication: Efinaconazole is an antifungal agent used to treat onychomycosis, a fungal infection of the nail.

name: Tavaborole
indication: Tavaborole is an antifungal agent used to treat onychomycosis, a fungal infection of the nail.

name: Tedizolid phosphate
indication: Tedizolid phosphate is an oxazolidinone class antibiotic that inhibits bacterial protein synthesis and is proven to be effective in the treatment of certain Gram-positive bacterial infections.

name: Finafloxacin
indication: Finafloxacin is indicated for the treatment of acute otitis externa (AOE) with or without an otowick, caused by susceptible strains of Pseudomonas aeruginosa and Staphylococcus aureus in patients age 1 year and older

name: Netupitant
indication: Netupitant is an antiemetic agent used in combination with palonosetron to prevent acute and delayed vomiting and nausea caused by chemotherapy.

name: Naloxegol
indication: Naloxegol is a peripherally-selective opioid antagonist used to treat opioid-induced constipation (OIC) in adult patients with chronic non-cancer pain.

name: Ceftolozane
indication: Ceftolozane is a cephalosporin antibiotic used to treat complicated intra-abdominal infections in combination with metronidazole, complicated urinary tract infections, and hospital-acquired pneumonia.

name: Ibrutinib
indication: Ibrutinib is an antineoplastic agent used to treat chronic lymphocytic leukemia, mantle cell lymphoma, and Waldenstrom's Macroglobulinemia.

name: Idelalisib
indication: Idelalisib is an antineoplastic kinase inhibitor used to treat chronic lymphocytic leukemia (CLL), relapsed follicular B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma (FL), and relapsed small lymphocytic lymphoma (SLL).

name: Acipimox
indication: Acipimox is a niacin derivative used in Fredrickson type IIb and type IV hyperlipoproteinemia.

name: Atosiban
indication: Atosiban is an inhibitor of oxytocin and vasopressin used to delay imminent preterm birth in pregnant adult women displaying specific clinical observations.

name: Avibactam
indication: Avibactam is a non-β-lactam β-lactamase inhibitor used in combination with ceftazidime for the treatment of complicated intra-abdominal infections, complicated urinary tract infections, and hospital or ventilator-acquired pneumonia.

name: Cannabidiol
indication: Cannabidiol is an active cannabinoid used as an adjunctive treatment for the management of seizures associated with Lennox-Gastaut syndrome or Dravet syndrome and symptomatic relief of moderate to severe neuropathic pain or other painful conditions, like cancer.

name: Ceritinib
indication: Ceritinib is an antineoplastic kinase inhibitor used to treat anaplastic lymphoma kinase (ALK)-positive metastatic non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) in patients with inadequate clinical response or intolerance to crizotinib.

name: Cobicistat
indication: Cobicistat is a CYP3A inhibitor used to increase the systemic exposure of atazanavir or darunavir in combination with other antiretroviral agents in the treatment of HIV-1 infection.

name: Vortioxetine
indication: Vortioxetine is a serotonin modulating antidepressant indicated for the treatment of major depressive disorder (MDD).

name: Trimetazidine
indication: Trimetazidine is a piperazine derivative indicated as an adjunct therapy in symptomatic treatment of stable angina pectoris.

name: Tibolone
indication: For the relief of post-menopausal symptoms and for the prevention of osteoporosis [L1724]

name: Tasimelteon
indication: Tasimelteon is a melatonin receptor agonist used to treat Non- 24-Hour Sleep-Wake Disorder.

name: Sodium oxybate
indication: Sodium oxybate is a central nervous system depressant used to treat cataplexy and excessive daytime sleepiness (EDS) associated with narcolepsy.

name: Palbociclib
indication: Palbociclib is an endocrine-based chemotherapeutic agent used in combination with other antineoplastic agents to treat HER2-negative and HR-positive advanced or metastatic breast cancer.

name: Olaparib
indication: Olaparib is a poly (ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) inhibitor used to treat ovarian cancer, breast cancer, pancreatic cancer, and prostate cancer.

name: Edoxaban
indication: Edoxaban is a novel oral anticoagulant used for reducing the risk of stroke and systemic embolism (SE) in patients with nonvalvular atrial fibrillation (NVAF).

name: Umeclidinium
indication: Umeclidinium is a long-acting muscarinic antagonist used as a long-term maintenance treatment of airflow obstruction in patients with chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD).

name: Lenvatinib
indication: Lenvatinib is a receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor used for the treatment of metastatic thyroid cancer, advanced renal cell carcinoma in combination with everolimus, and unresectable hepatocellular carcinoma.

name: Nintedanib
indication: Nintedanib is a triple angiokinase inhibitor indicated for the treatment of idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis, systemic sclerosis-associated interstitial lung disease, and in combination with docetaxel for non-small cell lung cancer.

name: Olodaterol
indication: Olodaterol is a long-acting beta2-adrenergic agonist used in the management of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD), including chronic bronchitis and/or emphysema.

indication: Tepotinib is an oral tyrosine kinase inhibitor targeted against MET for the treatment of metastatic non-small cell lung cancer in patients exhibiting MET exon 14 skipping mutations.

name: Futibatinib
indication: Futibatinib is a kinase inhibitor used to treat intrahepatic cholangiocarcinoma in previously treated adults.

name: Avapritinib
indication: Avapritinib is a selective tyrosine kinase inhibitor being investigated for the treatment of multidrug resistant gastrointestinal tumors.

name: Risdiplam
indication: Risdiplam is an oral mRNA splicing modifier used in the treatment of spinal muscular atrophy (SMA).

name: Ubrogepant
indication: Ubrogepant is an oral CGRP antagonist used in the acute treatment of migraine with or without aura.

name: Pafolacianine
indication: Pafolacianine is an optical imaging agent indicated in adult patients with ovarian cancer as an adjunct for intraoperative identification of malignant lesions.

name: Trilaciclib
indication: Trilaciclib is a CDK4 and CDK6 inhibitor to reduce the risk of chemotherapy induced myelosuppression.

name: Elexacaftor
indication: Elexacaftor is a small molecule CFTR corrector used in combination with tezacaftor and ivacaftor for the treatment of cystic fibrosis patients with one F508del-CFTR mutation.

name: Vericiguat
indication: Vericiguat is a soluble guanylate cyclase stimulator used to reduce heart failure-related hospitalization and cardiovascular death in patients with chronic systolic heart failure.

name: Belzutifan
indication: Belzutifan is an inhibitor of hypoxia-inducible factor 2α used as an antineoplastic in the treatment of certain cancers associated with von Hippel-Lindau (VHL) disease.

name: Benzhydrocodone
indication: Benzyhydrocodone is indicated, in combination with [acetaminophen], for the short-term management of acute pain requiring opioid therapy

name: Edotreotide gallium Ga-68
indication: Edotreotide gallium Ga-68 is a radioactive diagnostic agent used in PET scans for somatostatin receptor positive neuroendocrine tumors in adult and pediatric patients.

name: Prednisolone acetate
indication: Prednisolone acetate is a glucocorticoid used to treat a wide variety of endocrine, inflammatory, and immune conditions as well as for palliation of neoplastic conditions.

name: Adagrasib
indication: Adagrasib is a KRAS inhibitor indicated for the treatment of locally advanced or metastatic KRAS G12C-mutated non-small cell lung cancer in patients who have received at least one prior systemic therapy.

name: Sotorasib
indication: Sotorasib is an experimental KRAS inhibitor being investigated for the treatment of KRAS G12C mutant non small cell lung cancer, colorectal cancer, and appendix cancer.

name: Padeliporfin
indication: Padeliporfin is a vascular-acting photosensitizer used to treat low-risk prostate cancer in adults.

name: Brilliant blue G
indication: Brilliant blue G is a disclosing agent used in ophthalmological surgery to stain the internal limiting membrane (ILM).

name: Ferric maltol
indication: Ferric maltol is a complexed iron supplement used to treat iron deficiency in adults.

name: Ferric derisomaltose
indication: Ferric derisomaltose is an iron injection used in the treatment of iron deficiency anemia.

name: Selpercatinib
indication: Selpercatinib is a RET receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor for the treatment of RET-driven non-small cell lung cancer, medullary thyroid cancer, and thyroid cancer in appropriate patient populations.

name: Fluoroestradiol F-18
indication: Fluoroestradiol F-18 is a radiolabeled analog of estradiol used as a contrast agent in the PET imaging of estrogen receptor-positive breast cancer lesions.

name: Cedazuridine
indication: Cedazuridine is a cytidine deaminase inhibitor coadministered with the hypomethylating agent decitabine for the treatment of variable forms of myelodysplastic syndrome (MDS).

name: Pralsetinib
indication: Pralsetinib is a RET receptor tyrosine kinase inhibitor for the treatment of metastatic RET-driven non-small cell lung cancer.

name: Copper oxodotreotide Cu-64
indication: Copper oxodotreotide Cu-64 is a Cu labeled somatostatin analog used in positron emission tomography to detect certain types of neuroendocrine tumors.

name: Berotralstat
indication: Berotralstat is an inhibitor of plasma kallikrein used for prophylaxis of angioedema attacks in patients with hereditary angioedema.

name: Gallium Ga-68 gozetotide
indication: Ga 68 PSMA-11 is a radiopharmaceutical agent used in the diagnosis of prostate-specific membrane antigen (PSMA) positive lesions in male patients during positron emission tomography.

name: Atogepant
indication: Atogepant is an oral CGRP antagonist used for the preventative therapy of episodic migraine headaches.

name: Finerenone
indication: Finerenone is a nonsteroidal mineralocorticoid receptor antagonist indicated to lower the risk of eGFR decline, end stage kidney disease, cardiovascular death, heart attack, and hospitalization for heart failure in chronic kidney disease associated with type 2 diabetes.

name: Maralixibat
indication: Maralixibat is an ileal bile acid transporter inhibitor indicated to treat cholestatic pruritus in patients with Alagille syndrome.

name: Mitapivat
indication: Mitapivat is a pyruvate kinase activator used to treat hemolytic anemia in adults with pyruvate kinase (PK) deficiency.

name: Odevixibat
indication: Odevixibat is an ileal sodium/bile acid cotransporter inhibitor indicated in the treatment of pruritus in patients with progressive familial intrahepatic cholestasis.

name: Olutasidenib
indication: Olutasidenib is an isocitrate dehydrogenase-1 (IDH1) inhibitor indicated for the treatment of patients with relapsed or refractory acute myeloid leukemia with a susceptible IDH1 mutation as detected by an FDA-approved test.

name: Mobocertinib
indication: Mobocertinib is an oral kinase inhibitor targeted against EGFR and used in the treatment of NSCLC with EGFR exon 20 insertion mutations.

name: Melphalan flufenamide
indication: Melphalan flufenamide is a melphalan prodrug used to treat relapsed or refractory multiple myeloma.

name: Fosdenopterin
indication: Fosdenopterin is an exogenous form of cyclic pyranopterin monophosphate (cPMP) used as a replacement substrate in patients with molybdenum cofactor deficiency (MoCD) type A.

name: Serdexmethylphenidate
indication: Serdexmethylphenidate is a prodrug of the CNS stimulant dexmethylphenidate used as a first-line treatment for Attention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder (ADHD).

name: Deucravacitinib
indication: Deucravacitinib is a TYK2 inhibitor being investigated as a treatment for psoriasis.

name: Nirmatrelvir
indication: Nirmatrelvir is an oral protease inhibitor with emergency use authorization for the treatment of mild-to-moderate COVID-19.

name: Belumosudil
indication: Belumosudil is an oral inhibitor of rho-associated coiled-coil-containing protein kinases (ROCK) used in the treatment of chronic graft-versus-host disease (GVHD).

name: Lutetium Lu-177 vipivotide tetraxetan
indication: Lutetium Lu-177 vipivotide tetraxetan is a radioligand therapeutic agent used to treat prostate-specific membrane antigen (PSMA)-positive metastatic castration-resistant prostate cancer in adults.

name: Linzagolix
indication: Linzagolix is a selective gonadotropin-releasing hormone (GnRH) receptor antagonist used for the symptomatic treatment of uterine fibroids.

name: Gadopiclenol
indication: Gadopiclenol is a gadolinium-based contrast agent (GBCA) used with magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) to detect and visualize lesions with abnormal vascularity.
